### Surrogate Modeling

We apply the `interpret()` function to the GAM.
This step serves as a sanity check: if MID is effective, it should perfectly replicate the predictive behavior of the original GAM.

::: {#d7648dc4 .cell execution_count=5}
``` {.python .cell-code}
mid_glm = mid.MIDExplainer(
  estimator = fit_glm,
  link = "log"
)
mid_glm.fit(
  train_X,
  y = fit_glm.predict(one_hot_encode(train_X))
)
```

